      "cycles": 8,
      "note": "The i7 index sits on the top strand; the Index 1 primer anneals to the bottom strand and reads 5'->3' (rightward) into the 8 bp i7 sample index, outputting the top-strand index sequence. Each SI-GA- well is a mix of 4 base-balanced 8 bp indices.",
      "diagram": "5'-...AGATCGGAAGAGCACACGTCTGAACTCCAGTCACNNNNNNNNATCTCGTATGCCGTCTTCTGCTTG-3'\n3'-...TCTAGCCTTCTCGTGTGCAGACTTGAGGTCAGTGNNNNNNNNTAGAGCATACGGCAGAAGACGAAC-5'\n   5'-AGATCGGAAGAGCACACGTCTGAACTCCAGTCAC-------->  (reads 8 bp i7 index)"
    },
    {
      "read": "Read 2",
      "primer": "TruSeq Read 2: 5'-GTGACTGGAGTTCAGACGTGTGCTCTTCCGATCT-3'",
      "template": "top",
      "cycles": 25,
      "note": "TruSeq Read 2 primer anneals to the top-strand Read 2 adapter and is extended 5'->3' (leftward) across the spacers and the 15 bp feature barcode (antibody identity). >=25 cycles are recommended for Cell Surface Protein libraries; when pooled with 3' Gene Expression it is typically run at the GEX Read 2 length (~90 bp). The primer occupies the bottom-strand adapter position shown below.",
      "diagram": "5'-...TTGCTAGGACCGGCCTTAAAGCNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNAGATCGGAAGAGCACACGTCTGAACTCCAGTCAC...-3'\n3'-...AACGATCCTGGCCGGAATTTCGNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNNTCTAGCCTTCTCGTGTGCAGACTTGAGGTCAGTG...-5'\n                          <-------------------------------------3'-TCTAGCCTTCTCGTGTGCAGACTTGAGGTCAGTG-5'\n                        |9nt spacer||--15 bp feature barcode--||10nt spacer|   (Read 2 primer, reads FB)"
    }
